he ethnographic evocation of space and place, the honing of dialogue, and the crafting of character depict the drama of social life, and borrows techniques from film, poetry, and fiction to expand the appeal of anthropological knowledge and heighten its ability to connect the public to the idiosyncrasies of people and locale. Ultimately, Wisdom from the Edge underscores the importance of recognizing and applying indigenous wisdom to the social problems that threaten the future.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEthnologistsxAttitudes. 0aEthnologyxAuthorship. 0aEthnologyxMoral and ethical aspects. 0aEthnologyxPhilosophy. 4aCULTURAL STUDIES. 4aLITERARY STUDIES. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aethnography, indigenous thought, storytelling and ethnography, Sufi thought, anthropology and ethnography, anthropology and literature, ethnographic narratives.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311075183308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Education, Psychology, Comm 2023 Englishz978311131910008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Education, Psychology, Communication 2023z9783111318141oZDB-23-SEW40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501770883?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501770883423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501770883/original  a978-3-11-075183-3  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131910-0  EBOOK PACKAGE Education, Psychology, Comm 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-1